      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Media Model\n\nTwilite needs four distinct concepts here:\n\n1. **Image asset**: a raster image the graph can store inline temporarily, download locally, or save into repo assets.\n2. **Video asset**: a direct video file or stable hosted video URL. This is media, not just generic text.\n3. **Embed ref**: a live reference to something rendered through an embed node, such as YouTube, Vimeo, or another iframe source.\n4. **SVG graphic**: authored vector presentation living directly in node data as `data.svg`.\n\nThe important split is **asset vs presentation**:\n\n- assets answer: \"what binary or reference do we have?\"\n- nodes answer: \"how should Twilite render and edit it here?\"\n\nThat keeps image, video, and embeds honest without pretending every pasted thing is already durable, published, or editor-ready.\n\nAdd one more distinction:\n\n- **Raw footage** should begin life as a temporary or local-first video asset, not as an embed. It only becomes a published video surface after an explicit conversion or upload step.",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "media-authoring-declaration"
        }
      }
    },
